# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Planned

- Current runtime support remains Node.js only.
- Add first-class support for Deno environments.
- Add browser-oriented library build support.
- Improve workflows for building React-related libraries.

## [1.0.0] - 2026-03-05

### Added

- Node-based test suite for `susee.build`.
- Plugin pipeline support across dependency, pre-process, and post-process stages.
- Config options for per-entry `format`, `tsconfigFilePath`, and duplicate symbol handling.

### Changed

- Expanded README with API, configuration, limitations, and usage details.
- Stabilized dual-format output behavior for ESM (`.mjs`, `.d.mts`) and CommonJS (`.cjs`, `.d.cts`).
- Improved `package.json` update flow for `main`, `module`, `types`, and `exports` generation.

### Notes

- `susee` remains focused on local TypeScript dependency bundling and does not bundle `node_modules`.

## [0.1.0] - 2025-01-01

<!-- markdownlint-disable MD024 -->

### Added

- TypeScript bundler pipeline with dependency tree resolution.
- Dual output targets: CommonJS (.cjs) and ESM (.mjs) with type declarations.
- Automatic `package.json` updates for `main`, `module`, `types`, and `exports`.
- Post-process hook system with sync/async hooks.
- Built-in helper hooks: `banner-text` and `minify`.
- Subpath exports for `banner-text` and `minify`.

### Notes

- Bundling excludes `node_modules`.
- Entry export limitations: supports `export { ... }` and `export default Identifier` only.
- When both named and default exports exist, CommonJS output drops named exports.
